3:
A son who desires to learn about wisdom makes his father very happy;
\q2 but the son who is a companion of prostitutes will lose all his money
\q1

6:
A bad person sets a trap with his sin; then he falls into it; 
\q2 but one who does right is full of songs and joy.
\q1

7:
The one who does right stands up for the poor and defends them; 
\q2 but wicked people do not see the importance of standing up for the poor. 
\q1

8:
People who sneer and mock others are like those who set a city on fire; 
\q2 but those who help people get rid of their anger are wise.
\q1

10:
A murderer hates him who does everything right; 
\q2 and they seek to kill the one who has a good reputation.
\q1

17:
Discipline your child and he will help you and serve you;
\q2 you will truly rejoice over him.
\q1

23:
Any person who is proud will be humbled;
\q2 but the one who is humbled will be given honor.
\q1

24:
A person who helps a thief, hates himself;
\q2 he overhears the curse, but he does not say anything about it. 
\q1
